---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Careers at Cowaty — Join Our Digital Growth Team"
  description="Cowaty is a remote-first digital agency. We hire people who take ownership, love learning, and want their work to visibly move the needle. No open roles right now — but send your CV."
  canonicalPath="/careers"
  schemaType="WebPage"
>
  <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="careers-hero-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Careers</p>
      <h1 id="careers-hero-heading">Work at Cowaty</h1>
      <p>
        We build careers around impact, not job titles. If that sounds like where
        you want to be, keep reading.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="how-we-work-heading" style="padding-top: 5rem; padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Culture</p>
        <h2 id="how-we-work-heading">How We Work</h2>
        <p>
          These aren't values we wrote for a website and then forgot about.
          They're the rules we actually operate by.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="how-we-work-grid">
        <article class="work-pillar">
          <h3>Remote First</h3>
          <p>
            We've always been remote. It's not a perk we added — it's how the company
            was designed. You bring the discipline; we provide the trust, the tools,
            and the context you need to do great work from anywhere.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="work-pillar">
          <h3>Ownership Over Titles</h3>
          <p>
            Titles tell you where someone sits in a org chart. Ownership tells you
            what they actually care about. At Cowaty, you own your work end-to-end.
            That means decisions, mistakes, and wins all belong to you.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="work-pillar">
          <h3>Learning Is the Job</h3>
          <p>
            Digital marketing changes constantly. We expect everyone on the team
            to read, test, and share what they learn. You grow professionally here
            because you're constantly being challenged to figure things out.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="work-pillar">
          <h3>Impact Is Visible</h3>
          <p>
            You'll see the direct result of your work in client results, in revenue,
            and in how the company grows. We don't bury people in meetings.
            We protect deep work time and measure what actually matters.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section aria-labelledby="open-positions-heading" style="padding-top: 3rem; padding-bottom: 6rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-header">
        <p class="section-label">Open Positions</p>
        <h2 id="open-positions-heading">Current Openings</h2>
      </header>

      <div class="no-openings-box">
        <h3>No open roles right now</h3>
        <p>
          We don't have any listed positions at the moment, but we're always
          interested in people who are exceptional at what they do. If that's you,
          introduce yourself.
        </p>
        <div class="btn-row">
          <a
            href="mailto:careers@cowaty.com"
            class="btn btn-primary"
            aria-label="Send your CV to careers@cowaty.com"
          >
            Send Your CV
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://wa.me/94787460322"
            class="btn btn-outline"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="Message us on WhatsApp (opens in new tab)"
          >
            WhatsApp Us
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
